The paper introduces a new language for specifying object-oriented systems, which includes modalities for positive/negative examples and invariants. This suggests a focus on software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also mentions a formal verification technique based on Alloy, which is a tool commonly used in logic and automated reasoning (cs.LO). Additionally, the use of modalities suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and formal methods (cs.FL).
